# Discord Bot (VS Code Version)

A multi-module Discord bot built with Discord.js v13, featuring AI chat, music playback, photo tracking, keyword triggers, and server utilities.

## Features

| Module | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **AI Bot** | Conversational AI with per-user memory (SQLite), powered by OpenRouter |
| **Music** | Play audio from YouTube, Spotify, and SoundCloud in voice channels |
| **Photo Tracker** | Automatically tracks and stats image uploads per user/channel |
| **Word Trigger** | Responds to keywords with copypasta messages (toggleable per server) |
| **Info Retrieve** | Server/user info utilities and data export commands |
| **Stay Up** | Periodic pings to keep the bot alive on free hosting |

---

## Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) v16+
- A Discord bot token ([Discord Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications))
- An [OpenRouter](https://openrouter.ai/) API key (for AI features)

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/laeffy7403/Discord-Bot-Vscode-Ver.git
cd Discord-Bot-Vscode-Ver
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file in the root directory:

```env
DIS_TOKEN=your_discord_bot_token_here
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here
```

Start the bot:

```bash
node launch.js
```

---

## Commands

### AI Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `@bot <message>` | Chat with the AI (has per-user memory) |
| `ai--clearmemo` | Clear your AI conversation history |
| `ai--memostat` | View your conversation statistics |

### Music Commands
*(Must be in a voice channel)*

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `-play <song/url>` | Play from YouTube, Spotify, or SoundCloud |
| `-skip` | Skip the current song |
| `-stop` | Stop and clear the queue |
| `-pause` | Pause playback |
| `-resume` | Resume playback |
| `-queue` | Show the current queue |
| `-nowplaying` | Show info about the current song |
| `-volume <0–100>` | Set the volume |
| `-ask <question>` | Ask the AI assistant anything |

### Photo Tracker Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `-mystat` | Your photo upload stats |
| `-photostat @user` | Stats for a specific user |
| `-toposter` | Leaderboard of top photo contributors |
| `-serverstat` | Overall server photo statistics |
| `-channelstat` | Photo stats for the current channel |

### Keyword Control Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `-ton` | Enable keyword trigger responses |
| `-toff` | Disable keyword trigger responses |
| `-tstat` | Check current keyword toggle status |

### General
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `--help` | List all available commands |
| `-uptime` | Show how long the bot has been online |

---

## Project Structure

```
├── launch.js               # Entry point — loads all modules
├── debug.js                # Standalone API connection tester
├── package.json
├── .env                    # Secret tokens (not committed)
└── bot_modules/
    ├── f_ai_bot.js         # AI chat with SQLite memory
    ├── f_music.js          # Music playback (YT/Spotify/SoundCloud)
    ├── f_info_retrieve.js  # Server/user info and data export
    ├── m_photo_tracker.js  # Image upload tracking
    ├── m_stay_up.js        # Keep-alive pinger
    └── m_word_trigger.js   # Keyword trigger responses
```

---

## Notes

- This is the **VS Code (local)** version. A separate Replit version exists for cloud deployment.
- VS Code version uses port `3000`; Replit version uses port `3001`.
- AI memory is stored in `conversations.db` (SQLite, auto-created on first run).
- Photo stats are stored in `photos.db` (SQLite, auto-created on first run).

---

## Debugging

To test your API key and bot token connection without starting the full bot:

```bash
node debug.js
```

